<ITEM>fetters</ITEM>
<ITEM>gallows</ITEM>
<ITEM>goods</ITEM>
<ITEM>lungs</ITEM>
<ITEM>news <NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot"><HI>News</HI> is always plural and yet we always join to it a verb in the &s;ingular number; as, <HI>What is the news?</HI> &amp;c. This is cer|tainly an impropriety, however authori&s;ed by cu&s;tom.</NOTE></ITEM>
