</TABLE></P>
<P>Sometimes by the words <HI>male, female, man, maid,</HI> prefixed to the common noun; as, a male-child, a female game&s;ter, a man-&s;ervant, a maid-&s;ervant.</P>
<P>But the regular ending of nouns feminine is in <HI>e&s;s;</HI> as in the&s;e that follow.</P>
