<P>Note, <HI>Shall,</HI> in the &s;econd and third per&s;ons of this ten&s;e, is u&s;ed only when &s;ubjoined to &s;ome
<PB N="48" REF="018871_0047_0FA821604A6E16F8">
conjunction; as, "by the time <HI>that</HI> you &s;hall have been there an hour," &amp;c. and it denotes event merely.</P>
