<P>There <HI>are</HI> two or three of us. By ibid.</P>
<P>Nor <HI>thou</HI> that <HI>flinge&s;t</HI> me. By ibid.</P>
<P>I have con&s;idered <HI>what has</HI> been &s;aid. By ibid.</P>
<P><HI>Whomever</HI> the king fa|vours. By rule 9.</P>
<P>Tho&s;e <HI>whom</HI> he thought true to his party. By ibid.</P>
